<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-4460] SystemTable.setBootstrapState always sets bootstrap state to true</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-4460</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;    public static void setBootstrapState(BootstrapState state)&lt;/p&gt;
    {
        String req = &quot;INSERT INTO system.%s (key, bootstrapped) VALUES (&apos;%s&apos;, &apos;%b&apos;)&quot;;
        processInternal(String.format(req, LOCAL_CF, LOCAL_KEY, getBootstrapState()));
        forceBlockingFlush(LOCAL_CF);
    }

&lt;p&gt;Third parameter %b is set from getBootstrapState() which returns an enum, thus %b collapses to null/non null checks. This would seem then to always set it to true.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
